<h1 id="how-were-going-to-setup-the-game">How we‚Äôre going to setup the game</h1>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="text-align: left">Technique</th>
      <th style="text-align: left">Description</th>
      <th style="text-align: left">Sign</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left"><a href="http://whereareyourkeys.org/technique-glossary/#bridgelanguage">Bridge Language</a></td>
      <td style="text-align: left">We will be using sign language to provide a bridge between English and Koine Greek. This helps memory and also helps keep the meaning clear when words change form ‚Äì something that Greek words are apt to do. WAYK uses American Sign language, but emplys the grammar of the target language (in our case Greek) as described <a href="http://whereareyourkeys.org/technique-glossary/#signlanguage">here</a></td>
      <td style="text-align: left"><img src="https://whereareyourkeys.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/bridge-language.gif" alt="" /></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left"><a href="http://whereareyourkeys.org/technique-glossary/#obviously">Obviously</a></td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Do things so that the meaning is clear and unambigious</td>
      <td style="text-align: left"><img src="https://whereareyourkeys.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/obviously.gif" alt="" /></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left"><a href="http://whereareyourkeys.org/technique-glossary/#limit">Limit</a></td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Keep things as focused and simple as possible so that learners don‚Äôt get overwhealmed.</td>
      <td style="text-align: left"><img src="https://whereareyourkeys.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/limit.gif" alt="" /></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left"><a href="http://whereareyourkeys.org/technique-glossary/#bitesizedpiece">Bite Sized Pieces</a></td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Try to teach one small, simple, part of the language at a time. ‚ÄúLeaders throw Bite-Sized Piece to find out if players are ready to move on.‚Äù</td>
      <td style="text-align: left"><img src="https://whereareyourkeys.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/bite-sized-piece.gif" alt="" /></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left"><a href="http://whereareyourkeys.org/technique-glossary/#inthrees">In Threes</a></td>
      <td style="text-align: left">Do things three times to give people the repititions they need to understand and learn them.</td>
      <td style="text-align: left">¬†</td>
    </tr>
